-- Invensys Climbs in London After CEO Henriksson Says Company May Be Bought
-- B y   B e n e d i k t   K a m m e l
-- 2010-11-15T08:13:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/invensys-climbs-in-london-after-ceo-henriksson-says-company-may-be-bought.html
Invensys Plc advanced as much as 8.9
percent in London trading after the Daily Telegraph reported
that the company may be a takeover target by Chinese railcar
maker CSR Corp., citing Chief Executive Officer Ulf Henriksson.  The shares rose as much as 28.2 pence to 347 pence, the
most since Nov. 4. CSR has the “possibility” of buying
Invensys, the newspaper reported, citing the Invensys CEO.
Officials at CSR weren’t immediately available to comment on the
report when contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  